ally from thepresent moment to the previous one. Maybe I should not have panicked, shouldhave waited quietly for the stone of my limbs to regain some tingle offlesh. Instead, I performed, or imagined performing, a wild wrenchingmovement--and the globe did not bulge. I must have hung in a spread-eagleposition for a little while longer before ending supine on the intangiblesoil. <236>





